Recep Tayyip Erdogan is the President of Turkey. 
He has been in office since 2014 and was previously the Prime Minister of Turkey from 2003 to 2014. 
Erdogan is a member of the Justice and Development Party (AK Party), 
which he co-founded in 2001. 
He is known for his conservative and nationalist views, 
and has implemented a number of controversial policies during his time in office. 
Erdogan has been criticized for his crackdown on political opposition, 
media freedom, and human rights, as well as his involvement in foreign conflicts such as the Syrian Civil War. 
He has also faced allegations of corruption and abuse of power.
